params.newKernel_: Address of the new kernel contract.

returns.dependencies: Array of keycodes which represent modules that                      this policy depends on.

constructor.details: Instantiate this contract as a policy.

returns._0: The domain separator for the protocol.

params.metadata: Order metadata converted to a hash.

params.payload: Rent payload converted to a hash.

params.order: Rental order converted to a hash.

returns.requests: Array of keycode <> function selector pairs which represent                  permissions for the policy.

params.activate_: Whether to activate or deactivate the policy.

params.interfaceId: The interface ID to check against.

returns.validOrderMagicValue: A `bytes4` value to return back to Seaport.

changeKernel(address).notice: Points the adapter to reference a new kernel address. This function can         only be called by the active kernel, and is used to perform migrations by         telling all policies and modules where the new kernel is located before         actually performing the migration.

configureDependencies().notice: Upon policy activation, configures the modules that the policy depends on.         If a module is ever upgraded that this policy depends on, the kernel will         call this function again to ensure this policy has the current address         of the module.

getOrderMetadataHash((uint8,uint256,(add.notice: Derives the order metadata EIP-712 compliant hash from an `OrderMetadata`.

getRentPayloadHash((bytes32,(address),(u.notice: Derives the rent payload EIP-712 compliant hash from a `RentPayload`.

getRentalOrderHash((bytes32,(uint8,uint8.notice: Derives the rental order EIP-712 compliant hash from a `RentalOrder`.

getSeaportMetadata().notice: Returns Seaport metadata for this contract, returning the contract         name and supported schemas.

onERC1155BatchReceived(address,address,u.notice: Handles the callback when receiving multiple ERC1155 tokens.

onERC1155Received(address,address,uint25.notice: Handles the callback when receiving ERC1155 tokens.

onERC721Received(address,address,uint256.notice: Handles the callback when receiving ERC721 tokens.

requestPermissions().notice: Upon policy activation, permissions are requested from the kernel to access         particular keycode <> function selector pairs. Once these permissions are         granted, they do not change and can only be revoked when the policy is         deactivated by the kernel.

setActiveStatus(bool).notice: Allows the kernel to grant or revoke the active status of the policy.

supportsInterface(bytes4).notice: Returns whether the interface is supported.

tokensReceived(address,address,address,u.notice: Handles the callback when receiving ERC777 tokens.

validateOrder((bytes32,address,address,(.notice: Callback function implemented to make this contract a valid Seaport zone.         It can be considered the entrypoint to creating a rental. When a seaport         order specifies the create policy as its zone address, Seaport will call         this function after each order in the batch is processed. A call to         `validateOrder` is what kicks off the rental process, and performs steps         to convert a seaport order into a rental order which is stored         by the protocol.
